  "passageParts": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "People have speculated for centuries about a future without work. Today is no different, with academics, writers, and activists once again\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthat technology is replacing human workers. Some imagine that the coming work-free world will be defined by\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​: A few wealthy people will own all the capital, and the masses will struggle in an impoverished wasteland.\n A different and not mutually exclusive\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nholds that the future will be a wasteland of a different sort, one\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nby purposelessness: Without jobs to give their lives\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, people will simply become lazy and depressed.\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​, today’s unemployed don’t seem to be having a great time. One Gallup poll found that 20 percent of Americans who have been unemployed for at least a year report having depression, double the rate for\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 7
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nAmericans. Also, some research suggests that the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor rising rates of mortality, mental-health problems, and addiction\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\npoorly-educated, middle-aged people is a shortage of well-paid jobs. Perhaps this is why many\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nthe agonizing dullness of a jobless future.\n But it doesn’t\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfollow from findings like these that a world without work would be filled with unease. Such visions are based on the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof being unemployed in a society built on the concept of employment. In the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 13
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof work, a society designed with other ends in mind could\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nstrikingly different circumstances for the future of labor and leisure. Today, the\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof work may be a bit overblown. “Many jobs are boring, degrading, unhealthy, and a waste of human potential,” says John Danaher, a lecturer at the National University of Ireland in Galway.\n These days, because leisure time is relatively\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nfor most workers, people use their free time to counterbalance the intellectual and emotional\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nof their jobs. “When I come home from a hard day’s work, I often feel\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 18
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​,” Danaher says, adding, “In a world in which I don’t have to work, I might feel rather different” – perhaps different enough to throw himself\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 19
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\na hobby or a passion project with the intensity usually reserved for\n "
    },
    {
      "type": "blank",
      "blankId": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": " ​\nmatters."
    }
  ],
